at a time on the section that collapsed he said more than 300 
people were moving across it to enter a ferry when it gave way and 
that more than 3000 people were lined up behind them 
we had enough personnel to control the situation and 
instructed them to allow the passengers in batches of about 200 to 
300 but the crowd was too big and the platform gave way he said 
