<TEXT>
pullman co has agreed to 650 million buyout by 
the investment firm forstmann little amp co dropping an earlier 
agreement for a takeover by a managmentled group forstmann little 
announced sunday 
the firm which specializes in leveraged buyouts stated it 
would pay 925 cash per share for pullmans 419 million 
outstanding shares or about 38757 million assumption of 
existing debt and expenses will make the total price of the buyout 
about 650 million forstmann little stated 
the buyout was conditioned on pullman terminating its earlier 
agreement for a 775 per share buyout by a group led by thomas m 
begel the companys chairman and chief executive and henley 
manufacturing corp pullmans biggest shareholder with 9 percent 
of the companys outstanding shares 
pullman stock closed unchanged at 9 a share friday on the new 
york stock exchange 
i am pleased that pullmans stockholders will get the benefit 
of the 925 transaction price and am confident that by being one 
of the forstmann little group of companies new opportunities will 
be provided for pullmans employees begel said in a news release 
pullman based in princeton nj is a diversified manufacturer 
of industrial and engineered component products including truck 
trailers aircraft seating food service equipment weapons systems 
components refuse disposal equipment and fluid handling systems 
the acquisition of pullman is an opportunity for forstmann 
little to purchase a wellmanaged diverse group of industrial 
businesses which have strong niche market positions said 
nicholas c forstmann a general partner of forstmann little 
in a leveraged buyout a company is acquired mainly with 
borrowed funds that are repaid with money raised by the target 
companys cash flow or the sale of its assets 
the begel group had planned to sell a number of pullmans 
businesses and divisions to pay off debt incurred in its buyout 
</TEXT>
